      <h4> Foobar </h4>
      <p> 
        This Ruby program is an adaptation of a classic technical interview problem which displays sequences of the Foobar pattern.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="box">
    <pre><code class="language-ruby">
     prompt = &quot;How many items do you want to see?&quot;
     puts prompt 

     input= gets.chomp 

     digit = input.to_i

     array = []

     number = 0 

     while  number != digit 
     number = 1 + number 
    
     array &lt;&lt; &quot;#{number}&quot;.to_i

     end 

     array.each do |foobar|
     if foobar % 3 == 0 
     puts &quot;foo&quot;
     
     elsif foobar % 5 == 0 
     puts &quot;bar&quot;
     
     else puts foobar
     end
     
     end
